      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a single dose of ibuprofen can be a problem if your kidneys are already struggling, so don't underestimate the risk. For a mild headache, you should still be careful, but a 200mg dose might be okay if you are extremely careful. However, for a proper clearance, you should definitely run that through a quick check with your doctor, or you can try a simple dose of acetaminophen instead.",
